I went back to my program. The structure looked exactly like the TestVar program. But, of course, it wasn&#39;t. I realized that I was setting the value in the thread variable in the constructor of the thread. In the Embarcadero C++ environment (and maybe everywhere), constructors run in the context of the calling thread. In each case, that was the main thread so my thread variable was getting set each time to main thread&#39;s address.

